<h1>Simulation Player Controls</h1>
<p>A 'player control' allows a player to control a simulation variable, for example 
  the amount of money being spent on police forces, or on trash pick up. Frequently 
  something being tracked by the player, such as the number of rats in the city, 
  is not something that can be directly controlled by them. But they can control 
  other items, such as the budget of the 'rat extermination department.'</p>
